//aka partial order homomorphism//

A ''monotone function'' $$h: P \to Q$$ ($$P,Q$$ are [[posets|Partially ordered set]]) is a function such that $$\forall \,y \in P. x \leq y$$, implies that $$h(x) \leq h(y)$$